<div class="main-container container">
  <div class="img-div section-xsmall">
    <%= image_tag "logo_dark.png" %>
  </div>
  <div class="row">
    <form>
      <div class="col-md-10">
        <div class="form-group">
          {{input value=url class="form-control" placeholder="Please enter FHIR Server URL"}}
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-2">
        <button  {{action "submit"}} class="btn orange_btn">Begin</button>


      </div>
    </form>
  </div>
  <div class="row section-large">
    <div class="col-md-12">
      <div id="animation" class="palette"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-10">
      <p>Each FHIR Interface test will first generate a conformance statement. Based on a conformance, a given set of recommended tests will be shown to the user.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-2">
      <p style="float:right"> 1/5  &nbsp
      <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-backward" aria-hidden="true"></span> &nbsp
      <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-pause" aria-hidden="true"></span> &nbsp
      <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-forward" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>


  <div class="row section-medium">
    <div class="col-md-4">
      <div  class="tri-palette">
        <h4>Healthcare</h4>
        <p>Nationwide adoption of electronic health records (EHR) promises to improve the exchange of health data. Health data exchange should yield many benefits. However, successful exchange of computable health data is still relatively uncommon. FHIR is here to solve that problem.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
      <div class="tri-palette">
        <h4>Crucible</h4>
        <p>The role of standardized testing to promote interoperability cannot be underestimated. When standards are implemented without standardized testing, variability results. In order to facilitate the transition to standardized EHRâ€™s, Crucible has been developed as a testing tool to assure the interoperabliity of FHIR interfaces.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
      <div class="tri-palette">
        <h4>FHIR</h4>
        <p>FHIR stands for Fast Healthcare Interoperability Resource. FHIR, developed by HL7 (Health Level Seven) has recently emerged as the most likely candidate to fill the gap of todays current lack in the ability to exchange computable health data.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
